headline: FAMILY PLANNING IS UPHELD IN ROME; Improvement in Birth Control Foreseen by New Yorker at Population Conference

headline: BIRTH CONTROL APPROVED; Augustana Synod 1st Lutheran Body to Give Such Backing
MRS. SANGER TALKS TO JAPANESE DIET; Tells Legislators That Birth Control Could Solve Vital Overpopulation Problem
snippet: TOKYO, April 15 -- Mrs. Margaret Sanger, noted advocate of birth control, today became the first woman from the United States to testify before the Japanese Diet.

headline: SOVIET IRKS INDIA BY A DIG AT WEST; Charge That Birth Control Is Another 'Warmongers' Plot' Is Resented
snippet: NEW DELHI, India, Jan. 28 -- Soviet propaganda in India, which is particularly active at this time, came a rare cropper this week.
